"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "4208: land, as a divine responsibility",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4208",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Israel's land is a gift from God, though ultimately it remains under divine ownership. Life in the land is therefore characterised by both privilege and responsibility.</p>\n<h2>The land is a gift from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:5-Deut26:9\">DEU 26:5–26:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It is Israel's inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:1\">DEU 26:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:13\">EXO 32:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:21\">DEU 4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:38\">DEU 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:4\">DEU 15:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:10\">DEU 19:10</a></p>\n<h3>Eleven full tribes share the inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:52-Num26:55\">NUM 26:52–26:55</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Inherited land east of Jordan allotted by Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:33\">NUM 32:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh12:6\">JOS 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:8\">JOS 13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:15\">JOS 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:24\">JOS 13:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:29\">JOS 13:29</a></p>\n<h3>Inherited land west of Jordan allotted by Joshua and others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:17-Num34:29\">NUM 34:17–34:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:1\">JOS 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:13\">JOS 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:1\">JOS 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:20\">JOS 15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh16:4\">JOS 16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:11\">JOS 18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:1\">JOS 19:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:10\">JOS 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:17\">JOS 19:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:24\">JOS 19:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:32\">JOS 19:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:40\">JOS 19:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:51\">JOS 19:51</a></p>\n<h3>Levi receives no inheritance of land</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:62\">NUM 26:62</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:1\">DEU 18:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:14\">JOS 13:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:33\">JOS 13:33</a></p>\n<h3>Israelite households to hold their inheritance in perpetuity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:7-Num36:9\">NUM 36:7–36:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:3\">1KI 21:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:18\">EZK 46:18</a></p>\n<h2>The land remains under divine ownership</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:23\">LEV 25:23</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Responsibility to God for the land</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33-Matt21:46\">MAT 21:33–21:46</a></p>\n<h3>The tithe</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:30\">LEV 27:30</a></strong> <em>The tithe of the land's produce given to the LORD, is a kind of rent, a way of acknowledging his ownership.</em></p>\n<h3>Harvest festivals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:16\">EXO 23:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:15-Lev23:21\">LEV 23:15–23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:33-Lev23:43\">LEV 23:33–23:43</a></p>\n<h3>Sabbath rest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:1-Lev25:7\">LEV 25:1–25:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The Year of Jubilee</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:8-Lev25:13\">LEV 25:8–25:13</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Responsibility to fellow Israelites in the land</h2>\n<h3>Individual property rights to be respected</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:14\">DEU 19:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:17\">DEU 27:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:25\">PRO 15:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:28\">PRO 22:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:10\">PRO 23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:10\">HOS 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>Violation of these rights severely condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:8\">ISA 5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:17-1Kgs21:19\">1KI 21:17–21:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:19\">JOB 20:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:8-Ezek45:9\">EZK 45:8–45:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:2\">MIC 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:9\">MIC 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Responsibility to the poor in the land</h2>\n<h3>The fallow (sabbath) year</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:10-Exod23:11\">EXO 23:10–23:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:6-Lev25:7\">LEV 25:6–25:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:1-Deut15:3\">DEU 15:1–15:3</a> <em>Debts probably include the labour of a debtor's dependants, working to pay off his debt.</em></p>\n<h3>The Year of Jubilee</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:8-Lev25:13\">LEV 25:8–25:13</a></p>\n<h3>Harvesting conventions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:9-Lev19:10\">LEV 19:9–19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:22\">LEV 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:19-Deut24:22\">DEU 24:19–24:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:2-Ruth2:3\">RUT 2:2–2:3</a></p>\n<h2>The land reflects God's blessing and curse</h2>\n<h3>Blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:1-Deut28:6\">DEU 28:1–28:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:11-Deut28:12\">DEU 28:11–28:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:18-Lev25:19\">LEV 25:18–25:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:13-Deut11:15\">DEU 11:13–11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:9-Ps65:13\">PSA 65:9–65:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps67:5-Ps67:6\">PSA 67:5–67:6</a></p>\n<h3>Curse</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15\">DEU 28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:18\">DEU 28:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:21\">DEU 28:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:24-Lev18:28\">LEV 18:24–18:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:22-Lev20:24\">LEV 20:22–20:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:42-Lev26:45\">LEV 26:42–26:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:1\">1KI 17:1</a></p>",
